Shenzhen International to Buy 24% of Shenzhen Airlines for $121 Million

-- B y   J a m e s   R e g a n
-- 
2011-05-08T11:02:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-08/shenzhen-international-to-buy-24-of-shenzhen-airlines-for-121-million.html
Shenzhen International Holdings Ltd. (152) 
has agreed to pay 788.6 million yuan ($121 million) for a 24
percent stake in Shenzhen Airlines, according to a company
filing to the Hong Kong stock exchange today.  The deal will boost Shenzhen International’s ownership of
the carrier to 49 percent from 25 percent, it said. The stake is
being sold by Shenzhen Huirun Investment Co. Ltd., which has
been declared bankrupt in  China ’s courts and is in receivership.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Regan at 
 jregan19@bloomberg.net  